---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Editorial Policy" description="How Selcurate researches and produces content.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-h1 font-bold font-heading text-foreground mb-6">How We Research</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-foreground-muted mb-8">Last updated: April 2026</p>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>We Are Data Aggregators, Not Product Reviewers</h2>
      <p>
        Selcurate does not personally test products. We aggregate and analyze data from
        multiple sources to help you make informed decisions:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Manufacturer specifications and official product pages</li>
        <li>Aggregated user reviews from Amazon, Reddit, and forums</li>
        <li>Community feedback from relevant subreddits</li>
        <li>Price tracking across multiple retailers</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>AI Disclosure</h2>
      <p>
        Our articles are drafted with the assistance of AI tools and then reviewed and
        edited by our team. All product data, prices, and specifications are sourced from
        real data — never generated by AI. User sentiment sections are researched and
        written by our human editors based on real user reviews.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate Relationships</h2>
      <p>
        We earn commissions through affiliate links. Commission rates do NOT influence
        content, product selection, or presentation order. See our
        <a href="/disclosure/">full disclosure</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Content Updates</h2>
      <p>
        We regularly review and update our articles to ensure accuracy. Prices, availability,
        and product specifications change over time. Each article shows when it was last
        updated. If you notice outdated information, please
        <a href="mailto:hello@selcurate.com">let us know</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>How Products Are Ranked</h2>
      <p>
        Products in our guides are organized based on:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Aggregated user ratings across platforms</li>
        <li>Feature-to-price ratio</li>
        <li>Relevance to the specific use case being discussed</li>
        <li>Community sentiment from Reddit and forums</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Affiliate commission rates have zero influence on product ordering or recommendations.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
